"1275","</font></i></p>"
"1276","<p align=center style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:center;><b><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting"
"1277","Firm</font></b></p>"
"1278","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"1279","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>The"
"1280","Board of Directors and Shareholders </font></p>"
"1281","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>Dreyfus"
"1282","BNY Mellon Funds, Inc.:</font></p>"
"1283","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"1284","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>In"
"1285","planning and performing our audits of the financial statements of Dreyfus"
"1286","Global Emerging Markets Fund, Dreyfus Select Managers Long/Short Fund, Dreyfus"
"1287","Alternative Diversifier Strategies Fund, Dreyfus Yield Enhancement Strategy"
"1288","Fund, and Dreyfus Emerging Markets Debt U.S Dollar Fund (collectively, the"
"1289","&#8220;Funds&#8221;), each a series of Dreyfus BNY Mellon Funds, Inc., as of and for the"
"1290","year ended October 31, 2016, in accordance with the standards of the Public"
"1291","Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we considered the Funds&#8217;"
"1292","internal control over financial reporting, including controls over safeguarding"
"1293","securities, as a basis for designing our auditing procedures for the purpose of"
"1294","expressing our opinion on the financial statements and to comply with the"
"1295","requirements of Form N-SAR, but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion on"
"1296","the effectiveness of the Funds&#8217; internal control over financial reporting."
"1297","Accordingly, we express no such opinion.</font></p>"
"1298","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></p>"
"1299","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>Management"
"1300","of the Funds is responsible for establishing and maintaining effective internal"
"1301","control over financial reporting. In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates"
"1302","and judgments by management are required to assess the expected benefits and"
"1303","related costs of controls. A fund&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting"
"1304","is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability"
"1305","of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external"
"1306","purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles (GAAP). A"
"1307","fund's internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and"
"1308","procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable"
"1309","detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the"
"1310","assets of the fund; (2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are"
"1311","recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in"
"1312","accordance with GAAP, and that receipts and expenditures of the fund are being"
"1313","made only in accordance with authorizations of management and trustees of the fund;"
"1314","and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely detection"
"1315","of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition of a fund's assets that could"
"1316","have a material effect on the financial statements.</font></p>"
"1317","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"1318","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>Because"
"1319","of its inherent limitations, internal control over financial reporting may not"
"1320","prevent or detect misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of"
"1321","effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may"
"1322","become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree of"
"1323","compliance with the policies or procedures may deteriorate. </font></p>"
"1324","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;"
"1325","</font></p>"
"1326","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>A"
"1327","deficiency in internal control over financial reporting exists when the design"
"1328","or operation of a control does not allow management or employees, in the normal"
"1329","course of performing their assigned functions, to prevent or detect"
"1330","misstatements on a timely basis. A material weakness is a deficiency, or a"
"1331","combination of deficiencies, in internal control over financial reporting, such"
"1332","that there is a reasonable possibility that a material misstatement of the Funds&#8217;"
"1333","annual or interim financial statements will not be prevented or detected on a"
"1334","timely basis.</font></p>"
"1335","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"1336","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"1337","</DIV><HR noshade align=center width=100% size=2><DIV STYLE=page-break-before: always>&nbsp;</DIV><a name=page_2></a><a name=_bclPageBorder2></a><DIV STYLE=PADDING-RIGHT: 0%; PADDING-LEFT: 0%>"
"1338","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>Our consideration of the Funds&#8217; internal control over"
"1339","financial reporting was for the limited purpose described in the first"
"1340","paragraph and would not necessarily disclose all deficiencies in internal"
"1341","control that might be material weaknesses under standards established by the"
"1342","Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States).&#160; However, we noted"
"1343","no deficiencies in the Funds&#8217; internal control over financial reporting and their"
"1344","operations, including controls over safeguarding securities that we consider to"
"1345","be a material weakness as defined above as of October 31, 2016.</font></p>"
"1346","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:11.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
